Egyptian Stocks: Egyptian Resorts, Palm Hills Developments Move

-- B y   M a h m o u d   K a s s e m
-- 
2011-04-04T12:44:31Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-04/egyptian-stocks-egyptian-resorts-palm-hills-developments-move.html
Egypt ’s benchmark  EGX 30 Index (CASE) 
dropped the most since March 24, decreasing 1.2 percent to
5,493.83 at the 2:30 p.m. close in Cairo.  The following stocks rose or fell in Egypt. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Egyptian Resorts Co. (EGTS)   retreated as much as 2.3
percent before closing 0.8 percent lower at 1.32 Egyptian
pounds. The resorts developer reported a net loss of 9.4 million
pounds ($1.6 million) after a profit of 4.7 million pounds in
the previous year.  Palm Hills Development SAE (PHDC EY) dropped 2.9 percent to
2.71 pounds, paring yesterday’s 8.1 percent gain. The market
regulator rejected the plan by the country’s second-biggest
publicly traded real-estate developer to distribute one bonus
share for every 10 held.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mahmoud Kassem in Cairo at 
 mkassem1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  